    "Automatic scores appear to live on some sort of non-uniform scale of their own, which is yet another reason why they are Comparison of Automatic Evaluations against Human Evaluation (HOPE).",
    "not comparable to each other.",
    "The scale is compressed, and the difference between samples becomes statistically insignificant.",
    "• The margin of error for all three engines is about 6%, which is about the same as the difference between mean of the measurements for different engines.",
